319
0:13:10.26,000 --> 0:13:13,000
different languages spoken on Earth.

320
0:13:13.26,000 --> 0:13:15,000
Now you might say, well, this is just natural.

321
0:13:15.26,000 --> 0:13:18,000
As we diverge, our languages are naturally going to diverge.

322
0:13:18.26,000 --> 0:13:2,000
But the real puzzle and irony

323
0:13:20.26,000 --> 0:13:23,000
is that the greatest density of different languages on Earth

324
0:13:23.26,000 --> 0:13:27,000
is found where people are most tightly packed together.

325
0:13:27.26,000 --> 0:13:29,000
If we go to the island of Papua New Guinea,

326
0:13:29.26,000 --> 0:13:32,000
